Content: [dscrdeql] <RyanInSiam> @AndronicusBass-Founder I asked what other locales are on the potential list for assistance. I myself am located in Southeast Asia (as my name should indicate). Here in Thailand, our late king was a huge proponent of sustainability and self-sufficiency. Providing people with the knowledge and resources to build their local economy, so as to help themselves and one another was huge on his priority list. So, finding out about this project really caught my eye. üòÉ

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [dscrdeql] <AndronicusBass-Founder> Yeah, we went there in May at our own expenses to meet people in the crypto community and we met suppliers and local businesses as well as scouting for land. We saw some of the devastation caused by hurricane maria and people lost their homes and its estimated 4500 lost their lives. if at least we can build private storm shelters for people to escape to so we can help save lives is our dream. We will build homes for people for profit as we are a blockchain business, but a portion of profits go toward getting people into affordable, strong and energy efficient homes
